
# XOR Shellcode Obfuscator

## Description

This tool is a **Python CLI script** designed to **obfuscate shellcode using XOR**, a common technique in offensive security used to evade basic signature-based detection mechanisms.

The tool is intended to be used as **part of a payload chain**, where its role is to **prepare and obfuscate the shellcode** so that it can later be consumed by a **separate loader**, typically written in **C**, which is responsible for decrypting the shellcode in memory and executing it.

This script **does not execute shellcode**. It only performs obfuscation and outputs the encrypted shellcode in multiple formats.

---

## Usage

### General Syntax

```bash
python xorcrypt.py --in <input_file> --out <output_file> --key <key> --format <format>

```

## Command-Line Arguments

| Flag | Description |
|----|------------|
| `--in` | Input file containing raw shellcode |
| `--out` | Output file where encrypted shellcode will be written |
| `--key` | XOR key (single-byte hex value or multi-byte string) |
| `--format` | Output format: `raw`, `python`, or `c` |

---

## Examples

### Example commands

```bash

XORshellcodeofuscator.py --in shellcode.bin --out encrypted.bin --key 4er4efre --format c

XORshellcodeofuscator.py --in shellcode.bin --out encrypted.bin --key 0x22 --format python
```

### Output format Examples

#### C format

unsigned char buf[] = {0xa4, 0xf5, 0xe2, 0xa4, 0xf5, 0xf6, 0xe2, 0xf5, 0x05, 0xa5, 0x22, 0x8c, 0x4f, 0x66, 0x72, 0x65, 0x5c, 0x00, 0x1e, 0x58, 0x0a, 0x0e, 0x05, 0x0a, 0x46, 0x09, 0x16, 0x34, 0x65, 0x66, 0x72, 0xa9};

#### Python format

buf = [0xa4, 0xf5, 0xe2, 0xa4, 0xf5, 0xf6, 0xe2, 0xf5, 0x05, 0xa5, 0x22, 0x8c, 0x4f, 0x66, 0x72, 0x65, 0x5c, 0x00, 0x1e, 0x58, 0x0a, 0x0e, 0x05, 0x0a,0x46, 0x09, 0x16, 0x34, 0x65, 0x66, 0x72, 0xa9]










